snippet: State House members on Friday night chose not to call a vote, apparently because supporters of same-sex marriage did not have enough votes to pass the measure.
abstract: Illinois State House members choose not to call vote on whether to permit same-sex couples to wed, apparently because supporters of same-sex marriage do not have enough votes to pass measure in the Democratic-controlled House.
lead_paragraph: State House members on Friday night chose not to call a vote, apparently because supporters of same-sex marriage did not have enough votes to pass the measure.
